.Im MicroEmacs command|indent
.so me.tni
.TH indent-increase 3
.XI indent-increase - "Increase the line indentation"
.XI indent-decrease - "Decrease the line indentation"
.SH NAME
indent-increase \- Increase the line indentation
.br
indent-decrease \- Decrease the line indentation
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.Me "|indent-increase"
.I 
.B indent-increase
.Me "|indent-decrease"
.I n
.B indent-decrease
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B indent-increase
increases  the  indentation  of a line  or  selection  region  by the  numeric
argument \fIn\fR tab stops defined by 
.Ht $buffer-indent-width 5 .
If the argument is negative then the  indentation  is reduced by the specified
number of tab stops. The default when omitted is a single indentation level.
.PP
.B indent-decrease
operates in the same way as 
.B indent-increase
except the indentation is decreased.
.SH NOTES
.B indent-increase
and 
.B indent-decrease
are defined in \fCformat.emf\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht $buffer-indent-width 5 .
.ad
.FH
